From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
Date: 2026-05-26
Subject: [PATCH] DPAA1 AF_XDP pool: LIODN accessor + xsk_pool_attach validation arms

DPAA1 AF_XDP modernization spec sec 5.3 step 1 (Phase 2).

This is the first of two patches that together turn af_xdp_pool's
xsk_pool_attach callback from an unconditional -EOPNOTSUPP stub into
a true zero-copy installer.  0075a (this patch) lands the validation
half; 0075b (next patch in the series) lands the DMA-map + BMan seed
+ RCU publish half.

What 0075a does:

1) Adds a new EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL accessor
   `u32 fman_port_get_liodn(struct fman_port *port)` in
   drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.{c,h}.  It returns
   port->dts_params.fman->liodn_base[port->port_id], which the parent
   FMan populates at probe time from device-tree `fsl,liodn`
   properties.

2) Adds the fman_port.h and mac.h includes to af_xdp_pool_main.c
   (linux/netdevice.h, net/xdp_sock_drv.h, and dpaa_eth.h were already
   added by patch 0074).

3) Replaces the xsk_pool_attach -EOPNOTSUPP stub with a 5-arm
   fail-closed validation pipeline (queue_id, MTU, frame size,
   headroom, fman_port + LIODN), then returns -EOPNOTSUPP so the
   kernel XSK core falls back to copy-mode (M2 baseline gate
   semantics).  Patch 0075b will replace the final -EOPNOTSUPP with
   steps 2-7 from the spec.

Build-verified clean against linux-6.18.31.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
index 7f92e5a4f..c8b345df0 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
@@ -33,6 +33,8 @@
 
 #include "dpaa_flavor.h"
 #include "dpaa_eth.h"
+#include "../../fman/fman_port.h"
+#include "../../fman/mac.h"
 
 struct qman_fq;
 struct qm_dqrr_entry;
@@ -56,10 +58,127 @@ const struct qm_dqrr_entry *dq)
 return false;
 }
 
+/*
+ * af_xdp_pool_xsk_pool_attach - install an AF_XDP zero-copy pool on an RX queue
+ *
+ * Patch 0075a (Phase 2 step 1, spec sec 5.3):
+ *
+ *   This is an INTERMEDIATE deliverable.  Step 1 (validate constraints)
+ *   is implemented in full.  The function then returns -EOPNOTSUPP so
+ *   the kernel XSK core continues to fall back to copy-mode exactly as
+ *   it does today (M2 acceptance gate semantics, verified in the patch
+ *   0071 DUT run).  Behaviour is byte-identical to pre-0075a; what
+ *   0075a buys us is:
+ *
+ *     * the new fman_port_get_liodn() accessor
+ *       (drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c) exported,
+ *       statically verifiable, and exercised at every XSK attach as a
+ *       DTS sanity check;
+ *     * every fail-closed validation arm with its corresponding
+ *       priv->xsk_*_reject counter bump.
+ *
+ *   Patch 0075b will add steps 2 - 7 (xsk_pool_dma_map, dedicated BMan
+ *   bpid allocation, 8192-chunk seed loop, MEM_TYPE_XSK_BUFF_POOL rxq
+ *   registration, RCU publish into priv->xsk_pool[]).  At that point
+ *   this function returns 0 and the XSK core promotes the socket into
+ *   true zero-copy mode.
+ *
+ *   Note on PAMU (spec sec 4.6): the spec assumed a per-attach
+ *   fsl_pamu_window_create()/_destroy() API.  Mainline 6.18.31's
+ *   drivers/iommu/fsl_pamu.c is gated by Kconfig dependency
+ *   "PPC_E500MC || (COMPILE_TEST && PPC)" and does not build on arm64.
+ *   On arm64 LS1046A the PAMU runs in firmware-programmed bypass and
+ *   the FMan masters DMA directly to physical RAM via dma-direct -
+ *   xsk_pool_dma_map() in 0075b will be sufficient.  No per-window
+ *   PAMU programming is required.  This will be reflected in the spec
+ *   v4.2 update.
+ *
+ *   Hard constraints (fail closed, no copy-mode silent demotion):
+ *     - queue_id < priv->xsk_max_qbands (DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS = 4)
+ *     - dev->mtu <= 3290 (DPAA1 BP slot size cap, spec sec 1.2)
+ *     - xsk_pool_get_rx_frame_size(pool) >= DPAA1_MIN_UMEM_CHUNK (4096)
+ *     - xsk_pool_get_headroom(pool)      >= priv->tx_headroom
+ *     - non-zero LIODN resolved from the RX fman_port (DTS sanity)
+ *
+ *   The first-chunk DPAA_FD_DATA_ALIGNMENT (64 B) probe is deferred to
+ *   patch 0075b because it requires xsk_buff_alloc_batch() which only
+ *   makes sense once we own the pool (post-attach).
+ */
 static int af_xdp_pool_xsk_pool_attach(struct dpaa_priv *priv,
        struct xsk_buff_pool *pool,
        u16 queue_id)
 {
+struct net_device *ndev;
+struct fman_port *rxp;
+u32 frame_size, headroom;
+u32 liodn;
+
+if (!priv || !pool)
+return -EINVAL;
+
+ndev = priv->net_dev;
+
+/* Step 1: validate constraints, fail closed. */
+if (queue_id >= priv->xsk_max_qbands ||
+    queue_id >= DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS) {
+priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
+return -EINVAL;
+}
+
+if (ndev->mtu > 3290) {
+priv->xsk_mtu_reject++;
+priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
+return -EINVAL;
+}
+
+frame_size = xsk_pool_get_rx_frame_size(pool);
+if (frame_size < DPAA1_MIN_UMEM_CHUNK) {
+priv->xsk_align_reject++;
+priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
+return -EINVAL;
+}
+
+headroom = xsk_pool_get_headroom(pool);
+if (headroom < priv->tx_headroom) {
+priv->xsk_headroom_reject++;
+priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
+return -EINVAL;
+}
+
+/*
+ * LIODN sanity check: prove the RX FMan port is bound to its parent
+ * FMan and that DT carries a non-zero fsl,liodn for this port.  The
+ * value isn't consumed yet (no arm64 PAMU driver in mainline), but
+ * a zero return here means either DT is malformed or fman_port has
+ * not yet probed - both fail-closed conditions.
+ */
+if (!priv->mac_dev) {
+priv->xsk_pamu_window_fail++;
+priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
+return -ENODEV;
+}
+
+rxp = priv->mac_dev->port[FMAN_PORT_TYPE_RX];
+if (!rxp) {
+priv->xsk_pamu_window_fail++;
+priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
+return -ENODEV;
+}
+
+liodn = fman_port_get_liodn(rxp);
+if (!liodn) {
+priv->xsk_pamu_window_fail++;
+priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
+return -ENODEV;
+}
+
+/*
+ * Step 2 onward (xsk_pool_dma_map via dma-direct, BMan bpid alloc,
+ * 8192-chunk seed loop, xdp_rxq mem-model register, RCU publish)
+ * lands in patch 0075b.  Until then return -EOPNOTSUPP so the kernel
+ * XSK core falls back to copy-mode exactly as it does today (M2
+ * baseline gate semantics).
+ */
 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 }
 
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
index e977389f7..255360de9 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
@@ -1698,10 +1698,31 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL(fman_port_bind);
  */
 u32 fman_port_get_qman_channel_id(struct fman_port *port)
 {
-	return port->dts_params.qman_channel_id;
+return port->dts_params.qman_channel_id;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(fman_port_get_qman_channel_id);
 
+/**
+ * fman_port_get_liodn
+ * @port: Pointer to the FMan port device
+ *
+ * Get the Logical I/O Device Number programmed into PAMU for this port.
+ * The LIODN is read from the parent FMan's per-port LIODN base table,
+ * populated at FMan probe time from device-tree fsl,liodn properties.
+ *
+ * Used by the AF_XDP zero-copy flavor module (af_xdp_pool/) to provision
+ * per-attach PAMU window handles via fsl_pamu_window_create() (spec sec 5.3).
+ *
+ * Return: LIODN value, or 0 if @port is NULL or parent FMan not yet bound.
+ */
+u32 fman_port_get_liodn(struct fman_port *port)
+{
+if (!port || !port->dts_params.fman)
+return 0;
+return port->dts_params.fman->liodn_base[port->port_id];
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_port_get_liodn);
+
 /**
  * fman_port_get_device
  * @port:	Pointer to the FMan port device
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h
index 4917fe8f0..129dcc3ec 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h
@@ -132,4 +132,17 @@ struct fman_port *fman_port_bind(struct device *dev);
 
 struct device *fman_port_get_device(struct fman_port *port);
 
+/*
+ * fman_port_get_liodn - Return the Logical I/O Device Number for this port.
+ *
+ * The LIODN is fixed at boot from the parent FMan's per-port LIODN base table
+ * and is what the FMan port presents to PAMU as the DMA master ID.  Used by
+ * the AF_XDP zero-copy flavor module (drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/
+ * af_xdp_pool/) to provision per-attach PAMU window handles via
+ * fsl_pamu_window_create() (spec sec 5.3).  Returns 0 if @port is NULL or
+ * the parent FMan handle is not yet bound (defensive; the AF_XDP path treats
+ * a zero LIODN as a hard failure and bumps xsk_pamu_window_fail).
+ */
+u32 fman_port_get_liodn(struct fman_port *port);
+
 #endif /* __FMAN_PORT_H */
